body.p: Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the simvastatin in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. Due to total absorption no simvastatin reaches the feces. (~60% Cheng1993, ~61-85% Vickers1990a, probably bioavailability).

ul.li: Model structure only works for complete absorption, i.e., F=1.0. Otherwise extension with fecal excretion required.

body.p: Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the simvastatin metabolites in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. This parameter determines how much of the simvastatin metabolites is excreted in every round of the enterohepatic circulation.
F_abs_simmets of dose is absorbed. (1-F_abs_simmets) is excreted in feces.
